<h1>Annual Parkinson’s Disease Therapeutics Conference</h1>
<p><img src="/files/pdtherapeutics.png" style="width: 100%;" /></p>
<p><strong>The Parkinson's Disease Therapeutics Conference</strong> is The Michael J. Fox Foundation's annual scientific conference and the only drug development conference in the world focused exclusively on Parkinson’s disease (PD). The Eighth Annual PD Therapeutics Conference will be held on <strong>October 29, 2014 in a <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>new location</em></span>: Convene Midtown East in New York City.</strong></p>
<p></p>
<p class="p1">Registration and information about the program and speakers will be available this summer. Get updates about this conference and other MJFF research activities by signing up for our <a href="https://secure3.convio.net/mjff/site/SPageNavigator/research_email_signup.html" class="orange bold"><strong>research newsletter.</strong></a></p>
<h2>About the PD Therapeutics Conference</h2>
<p>The conference brings together approximately 300 research and business development professionals from both academia and industry and showcases the most exciting and innovative research from MJFF’s research portfolio. Novel advances in basic and translational research from both academic and industry labs are highlighted through speaker presentations and a poster session. The event is a platform for field leaders to share new and unpublished results and for fostering new relationships and collaborations.</p>
<p></p>
